FBIS4-41115 "drsov120_g_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-120 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus Said To Reach Agreement on Oil Credit Said To Reach Agreement on Oil Credit WS2206094394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1600 GMT 21 Jun 94 WS2206094394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network Belarusian BFN [Text] As has already been reported, Belarusian Prime Minister Vyachaslaw Kebich is on a short working visit to Austria. The intention of the visit is to sign a document securing a $100 million credit to our Republic from the Austrian Government. Those credits will be used to purchase Russian oil to meet Belarusian needs and fund its subsequent processing at the Novopolotsk Oil Refinery. It is planned that a [word indistinct] portion of the gasoline and other oil products will be sold on European markets, which will provide hard currency to repay the credit. Vyachaslaw Kebich held a prolonged meeting with Austrian Chancellor Franz Vranitzky. Also discussed at the negotiations was the issue of Belarus joining the GATT. Agreement was reached on all issues.
